Use [`XInclude`][1].

Your schema.xml may already contain `xi:include` code chunks (to be uncommented), eg. 

      &lt;fields&gt;
        &lt;!-- regular/dynamic fields definitions... --&gt;
      &lt;/fields&gt;

      &lt;xi:include href=&quot;schema_fields_spanish.xml&quot; xmlns:xi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xi:fallback&gt;&lt;/xi:fallback&gt;
      &lt;/xi:include&gt;

You can see an example of this in Solr configuration for TYPO3 search (e.g. [for Korean][2]).

Note, however, that recent Solr versions use managed-schema, which gets rewritten on any change. That means all the XIncludes will get pulled-in and rearranged. If you are not happy about that and prefer to version-control your schema file, you can disable that in solrconfig.xml with [Schema Factory configuration][3].


  [1]: https://www.w3.org/TR/xinclude/
  [2]: https://github.com/TYPO3-Solr/ext-solr/blob/master/Resources/Private/Solr/configsets/ext_solr_9_0_0/conf/korean/schema.xml#L30-L36
